.TH simple_shell 1 "Decembre 2023" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
.B simple_shell
Creation of a simple UNIX command interpreter.

.SH LIBRARIES
simple_shell use <stdio.h> <stdlib.h> <string.h> <unistd.h> <sys/wait.h> <sys/types.h> and <sys/stat.h>.

.SH SYNOPSIS
simple_shell is a command interpreter for UNIX systems. 
It is designed to provide a simple and intuitive interface for executing commands. 
The program uses various libraries including <stdio.h>, <stdlib.h>, <string.h>, <unistd.h>, <sys/wait.h>, <sys/types.h>, 
and <sys/stat.h>. It can be used to execute commands and scripts. 
The main function of the simple_shell program returns an integer value. 

.SH USAGE
After compiled, you can lauch the shell in interactive mode by typing ./hsh in the terminal you use.

.SH MODE
The simple_shell can be use in two differents modes : interactive mode with the prompt, or non-interactive mode.
.IP Exemples
.B $cisnotfun ls
.B echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh

.SH RETURN VALUE
The main function of the simple_shell program returns an integer value. 
A return value of 0 indicates successful execution of the program, while a non-zero return value indicates an error or abnormal termination.

.SH EXIT
The `exit` command is used to terminate the simple_shell program.

.SH EXEMPLES 
The simple_shell search in the shell building if the command exist if it begins with "/".
It can take "/bin/ls" command or "ls" command.
.IP Exemples
.B $cisnotfun ls

.B $cisnotfun /bin/ls

.SH BUGS
No known bugs.

